'''Osborne Hart''' (born 1952) is an American socialist activist. Hart was the vice-presidential nominee of the [[Socialist Workers Party (United States)|Socialist Workers Party]] in the [[United States presidential election, 2016|2016 presidential election]]. He has run for several other offices, including for [[Philadelphia mayoral election, 2015|mayor of Philadelphia in 2015]].<ref name="KYWTV">{{cite news|url=http://philadelphia.cbslocal.com/2015/08/03/63-year-old-walmart-employee-philadelphia-mayor/|title=63-Year-Old Walmart Employee Makes His Case For Philadelphia Mayor|date=August 3, 2015|publisher=[[KYW-TV]]|accessdate=14 February 2016}}</ref>

Hart's father was a career soldier and he traveled extensively as a youth. His activism began in the 1960s during the [[Civil Rights Movement]]. He has also been active in the solidarity movement with socialist Cuba and other political movements.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.themilitant.com/2016/8007/800702.html|title=The SWP candidates|date=February 22, 2016|work=[[The Militant]]|accessdate=14 February 2016}}</ref>

