'''Vic Garth''' (9 September 1912 - 10 April 2005) was [[town crier]] in [[Hobart]], [[Tasmania]], for more than 20 years, until his death in April 2005 at the age of 92. Though battling cancer for several years, he continued to greet cruise ships as they arrived, and frequently appeared at Hobart's [[Salamanca Market]] on Saturdays. In 2003 he became known as the oldest town crier in the world.<ref>{{Cite web|url= http://www.abc.net.au/news/items/200507/1426313.htm?tasmania|title=Hobart seeks passionate loudmouths|work=abc.net.au|publisher=ABC Tasmania|accessdate=30 April 2010|date=30 July 2005}}</ref>
